# <%= current_page.data.title %>

## Quick start (for whoever spotted the issue)

This document assumes the user has a PagerDuty account and is part of the Analytical Platform team. To use the Slack features, the user must authorise the PagerDuty application in Slack.

1. Assume **Incident Lead (IL)** unless someone else is already acting.
1. Start a single Slack thread in **#analytical-platform** with a clear title (e.g. `Airflow Autoscaling Incident 🧵`) and keep all communications in that thread.
1. Declare the incident on the **PagerDuty Status Page** (see checklist below) and set a **Next update** time.
1. Classify the priority (**P1–P4**) using the table below.
1. Assign a **Comms Lead (CL)** and identify **Subject Matter Responders (SMRs)**.
1. Create and link the incident report using the Incident Report template.

---

## Scope & Context

**Service**

Analytical Platform (ingestion, storage, compute, networking, identity, etc.)

**Status visibility**

- External updates via PagerDuty Status Page
- Internal visibility via Slack

**Source of truth**

- Single Slack incident thread
- Incident Report

