## Incident Priority (per GDS Way)

| Priority | Classification | Example | Target Response Time | Update Frequency |
|----------|----------------|---------|----------------------|------------------|
| **P1** | Critical | Complete outage or ongoing unauthorised access | 20 minutes (office & out-of-hours) | Every 1 hour |
| **P2** | Major | Substantial degradation of service | 60 minutes (office & out-of-hours) | Every 2 hours |
| **P3** | Significant | Intermittent/degraded service due to platform issue | 2 hours (office hours only) | Once after 2 business days |
| **P4** | Minor | Component failure not immediately impacting a service; unsuccessful DoS attempt | 1 business day (office hours only) | Once after 5 business days |

> **Note**
>
> Analytical Platform currently does not have any SLAs or an out-of-hours support requirement. The response times and update frequencies above relate to standard working days.
>
> Use judgement to escalate or de-escalate as new information emerges.

